value.value: A proprietary immunoenzymatic assay system designed to measure prostate-specific antigen in serum samples.
A proprietary system designed to measure protein-complexed prostate-specific antigen (cPSA) in the blood.
A methanol-water solution for the preservation of cervical cells for automated Pap testing.
A partial fixative used for the preparation of cytology specimens from sputum samples.
A manufacturer of reagents and instruments for the separation, purification, and analysis of biospecimens.
A manufacturer of in vitro diagnostic instrument systems.
A manufacturer of biomedical laboratory instruments.
A manufacturer of instruments and assay systems for clinical analysis and diagnosis.
Blood in the feces that is not visibly apparent.
A colon that is longer than a normal colon, with additional bends and twists.
Abnormally low level of immature red blood cells in the blood.
Abnormally high level of red blood cells in the blood.
Abnormally low level of eosinophils in the blood.
Abnormally low level of basophils in the blood.
Abnormally low level of monocytes in the blood.

A microscopic finding indicating the presence of scattered islands of pathologic processes in a tissue sample.  The pathologic processes may refer to various abnormalities, including the presence of islands of malignant cells, presence of necrotic foci, and presence of islands of connective tissue that lack fibers.
Resection of the rectum for cancer through an incision in the lower abdomen.

Irreparable damage to multiple organs/systems which is the result of chronic complications of diabetes.  The affected organs/systems include the cardiovascular system, kidneys, eyes, nervous system, joints and feet.

A CT scan finding in the lungs indicating the presence of hazy areas of attenuation in the air spaces.  It is caused by interstitial fibrosis, alveolar collapse, edema, inflammation, or cancer with lepidic spread.
A term that refers to a pulmonary nodule in which part of the ground-glass opacity completely obscures the parenchyma on CT scan examination.

label.value: Abnormal Colorectal Exam, Suspicious for Malignancy

value.value: A clinical finding indicating the presence of a firm, indurated, or nodular lesion, which is suspicious for malignancy, during colorectal examination.

label.value: Abnormal Colorectal Exam, Highly Suspicious for Malignancy

value.value: A clinical finding indicating the presence of a lesion, which is highly suspicious for malignancy, during colorectal examination.
A rare autoimmune disorder in which patients present with overlapping symptoms of systemic scleroderma and polymyositis or dermatomyositis.
Indicates that a phlebotomist was unable to find or penetrate a blood vessel or was unable to acquire a blood sample following a successful vein stick.
Refers to an underlying pathologic process that has not been identified.
Indicates that an individual is unable to self-collect a urine specimen.

A surgical procedure performed in patients with benign prostatic hyperplasia.  An instrument is inserted in the urethra that generates electric current or laser beam, which create incisions in the bladder neck. The incisions result in decreased resistance to the flow of the urine out of the urinary bladder.
An endoscopic therapeutic procedure in which a balloon device is used to dilate a narrowed lumen.
A morphologic qualifier indicating that a neoplasm is of borderline malignancy.
A morphologic qualifier indicating that the grade of a neoplasm cannot be assessed.

A granuloma that is not associated with necrotic changes.  The majority of cases are of non-infectious origin.  Causes include sarcoidosis, hypersensitivity pneumonitis, drug reactions, and Crohn disease.
A granuloma that contains areas of necrosis.  The majority of cases are of infectious origin.
A morphologic finding indicating the presence of single cells or small groups of cells with prominent eosinophilic cytoplasmic granules in a tissue sample.
A morphologic finding indicating the presence of a malignant cellular infiltrate with poorly defined glands in a tissue sample.
A morphologic finding indicating the presence of an epithelial infiltrate resembling the cells of the transition zone of the prostate gland.
A cyst that is formed because of the blockage of the duct of a glandular organ. This results in the retention of the glandular secretions.
A proprietary high-throughput chemiluminescent immunoassay system manufactured by Siemens.
A proprietary integrated chemistry system for high-throughput integration of chemistry and immunoassay testing manufactured by Siemens.
A proprietary instrument for immunoassay analysis manufactured by Siemens.
Abnormally high level of fibrinogen in the blood.
A proprietary immunodiagnostic chemiluminescent system manufactured by Ortho Clinical Diagnostics.
Abnormally heavy or prolonged loss of blood.
Bruising that is disproportionately high to the amount of trauma received or reported.
Material that has been treated so as to be largely uniform throughout.
A cell sample collected and compacted by centrifugation of a liquid suspension.
